{
  "appId": "gmail",
  "name": "Gmail",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "type": "integration",
  "description": "Gmail integration with per-user sync. Owns email data (messages, threads, participants, attachments). Consumer apps read via the collections API.",
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "clientId": { "type": "string", "description": "Google OAuth 2.0 Client ID", "platformSecret": "GMAIL_CLIENT_ID" },
      "clientSecret": { "type": "string", "description": "Google OAuth 2.0 Client Secret", "platformSecret": "GMAIL_CLIENT_SECRET" },
      "proxyToken": { "type": "string", "description": "Managed proxy HMAC token (managed mode only)", "platformSecret": "GMAIL_PROXY_TOKEN" },
      "baseUrl": { "type": "string", "description": "Managed proxy base URL (managed mode only)", "platformSecret": "GMAIL_BASE_URL" },
      "enableModifyScope": { "type": "boolean", "description": "Opt in to gmail.modify scope (requires Google security review)", "default": false },
      "pubsubTopicName": { "type": "string", "description": "Cloud Pub/Sub topic for push notifications" }
    }
  },
  "userAuth": { "type": "redirect" },
  "actions": [
    {
      "id": "send_email",
      "name": "Send Email",
      "description": "Send an email. Supports threading, attachments, aliases. The sent message is automatically persisted in gmail.messages.",
      "inputSchema": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "to": { "oneOf": [{ "type": "string" }, { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }] },
          "cc": { "oneOf": [{ "type": "string" }, { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }] },
          "bcc": { "oneOf": [{ "type": "string" }, { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }] },
          "subject": { "type": "string" },
          "text": { "type": "string" },
          "html": { "type": "string" },
          "attachments": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "object", "properties": { "filename": { "type": "string" }, "content": { "type": "string" }, "contentType": { "type": "string" } }, "required": ["filename", "content"] } },
          "inReplyTo": { "type": "string" },
          "references": { "oneOf": [{ "type": "string" }, { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } }] },
          "threadId": { "type": "string" },
          "from": { "type": "string" }
        },
        "required": ["subject"]
      },
      "outputSchema": { "type": "object", "properties": { "messageId": { "type": "string" }, "threadId": { "type": "string" }, "headerMessageId": { "type": "string" } } }
    },
    {
      "id": "create_draft",
      "name": "Create Draft",
      "description": "Create a draft email (same input as send_email).",
      "inputSchema": { "$ref": "#/actions/0/inputSchema" },
      "outputSchema": { "type": "object", "properties": { "draftId": { "type": "string" }, "messageId": { "type": "string" }, "threadId": { "type": "string" }, "headerMessageId": { "type": "string" } } }
    },
    {
      "id": "get_attachment",
      "name": "Get Attachment",
      "description": "Fetch attachment bytes by message and attachment ID.",
      "inputSchema": { "type": "object", "properties": { "messageId": { "type": "string" }, "attachmentId": { "type": "string" } }, "required": ["messageId", "attachmentId"] },
      "outputSchema": { "type": "object", "properties": { "data": { "type": "string" }, "size": { "type": "integer" } } }
    },
    {
      "id": "sync_connect",
      "name": "Start Sync",
      "description": "Initialize sync for the current user. Creates a sync_cursor, registers a 5-min cron, and triggers the first full sync.",
      "inputSchema": { "type": "object" },
      "outputSchema": { "type": "object", "properties": { "cursor_id": { "type": "string" }, "handle": { "type": "string" } } }
    },
    {
      "id": "sync_disconnect",
      "name": "Stop Sync",
      "description": "Disable sync for the current user. Removes cron but keeps synced data.",
      "inputSchema": { "type": "object" },
      "outputSchema": { "type": "object", "properties": { "ok": { "type": "boolean" } } }
    },
    {
      "id": "sync_now",
      "name": "Trigger Sync",
      "description": "Trigger an immediate sync for the current user.",
      "inputSchema": { "type": "object" },
      "outputSchema": { "type": "object", "properties": { "triggered": { "type": "boolean" } } }
    },
    {
      "id": "get_profile",
      "name": "Get Profile",
      "description": "Return the user's email address and current historyId.",
      "inputSchema": { "type": "object" },
      "outputSchema": { "type": "object", "properties": { "emailAddress": { "type": "string" }, "historyId": { "type": "string" } } }
    },
    {
      "id": "list_send_as",
      "name": "List Send-As Aliases",
      "description": "List verified send-as addresses for the user.",
      "inputSchema": { "type": "object" },
      "outputSchema": { "type": "object", "properties": { "sendAs": { "type": "array" } } }
    },
    {
      "id": "watch",
      "name": "Watch Mailbox",
      "description": "Register a Pub/Sub push subscription.",
      "inputSchema": { "type": "object", "properties": { "topicName": { "type": "string" }, "labelIds": { "type": "array", "items": { "type": "string" } } } },
      "outputSchema": { "type": "object", "properties": { "historyId": { "type": "string" }, "expiration": { "type": "integer" } } }
    },
    {
      "id": "stop_watch",
      "name": "Stop Watch",
      "description": "Cancel push subscription.",
      "inputSchema": { "type": "object" },
      "outputSchema": { "type": "object" }
    }
  ],
  "webhooks": ["push_notification"],
  "dataContract": [
    {
      "entityName": "messages",
      "fields": [
        { "name": "external_id",        "type": "text", "unique": true },
        { "name": "thread_external_id",  "type": "text" },
        { "name": "header_message_id",   "type": "text", "unique": true },
        { "name": "user_id",            "type": "text", "required": true },
        { "name": "subject",            "type": "text" },
        { "name": "body_text",          "type": "text" },
        { "name": "body_html",          "type": "text" },
        { "name": "snippet",            "type": "text" },
        { "name": "internal_date",      "type": "timestamp" },
        { "name": "label_ids",          "type": "text" },
        { "name": "in_reply_to",        "type": "text" },
        { "name": "references",         "type": "text" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "entityName": "threads",
      "fields": [
        { "name": "external_id",        "type": "text", "unique": true },
        { "name": "user_id",            "type": "text", "required": true },
        { "name": "subject",            "type": "text" },
        { "name": "last_message_at",    "type": "timestamp" },
        { "name": "message_count",      "type": "number" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "entityName": "participants",
      "fields": [
        { "name": "message_id",  "type": "entity_link", "onDelete": "cascade", "references": { "entity": "messages", "field": "id" }, "required": true },
        { "name": "address",     "type": "text", "required": true },
        { "name": "name",        "type": "text" },
        { "name": "role",        "type": "text", "required": true, "enum_values": ["from", "to", "cc", "bcc"] }
      ]
    },
    {
      "entityName": "attachments",
      "fields": [
        { "name": "message_id",   "type": "entity_link", "onDelete": "cascade", "references": { "entity": "messages", "field": "id" }, "required": true },
        { "name": "external_id",  "type": "text", "required": true },
        { "name": "filename",     "type": "text" },
        { "name": "mime_type",    "type": "text" },
        { "name": "size",         "type": "number" },
        { "name": "content_id",   "type": "text" },
        { "name": "is_inline",    "type": "boolean" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "entityName": "sync_cursors",
      "fields": [
        { "name": "user_id",          "type": "text", "required": true },
        { "name": "handle",           "type": "text" },
        { "name": "handle_aliases",   "type": "text" },
        { "name": "cursor",           "type": "text" },
        { "name": "status",           "type": "text", "enum_values": ["idle", "syncing", "needs_reauth", "failed_temporary", "failed_permanent"] },
        { "name": "sync_stage",       "type": "text", "enum_values": ["list_fetch", "messages_import"] },
        { "name": "last_synced_at",   "type": "timestamp" },
        { "name": "throttle_count",   "type": "number" },
        { "name": "throttle_after",   "type": "timestamp" },
        { "name": "cron_id",          "type": "text" },
        { "name": "watch_expires_at", "type": "timestamp" },
        { "name": "enabled",          "type": "boolean" }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "permissions": {
    "permissions": [
      { "key": "messages.read",      "description": "Read synced emails" },
      { "key": "messages.write",     "description": "Write emails (internal sync)" },
      { "key": "threads.read",       "description": "Read email threads" },
      { "key": "threads.write",      "description": "Write threads (internal sync)" },
      { "key": "participants.read",  "description": "Read email participants" },
      { "key": "participants.write", "description": "Write participants (internal sync)" },
      { "key": "attachments.read",   "description": "Read attachment metadata" },
      { "key": "attachments.write",  "description": "Write attachments (internal sync)" },
      { "key": "sync_cursors.read",  "description": "Read sync state" },
      { "key": "sync_cursors.write", "description": "Manage sync state" }
    ]
  },
  "instructions": "Gmail integration v1.0 -- owns email data.\n\nThis integration syncs emails from connected Gmail accounts and stores them in its own entities (messages, threads, participants, attachments). Consumer apps (CRM, helpdesk, prospection) read data via the collections API:\n\n  GET /api/v1/apps/gmail/collections/messages?where={...}\n  GET /api/v1/apps/gmail/collections/participants?where={address: {$eq: \"user@example.com\"}}\n\nSync is managed by the integration itself:\n- `sync_connect` initializes sync + creates a 5-min cron\n- `sync_disconnect` stops the cron\n- `sync_now` triggers immediate sync\n\nSend:\n- `send_email` composes and sends, then auto-persists the sent message in gmail.messages\n- Supports threading (threadId + inReplyTo + references), attachments (base64), aliases (from)\n\nAttachments:\n- Metadata stored in gmail.attachments at sync time\n- Bytes fetched lazily via `get_attachment` action\n\nError contract:\n- All actions return {ok: true, data} or {ok: false, error: {code, message, retryAfter?}}\n- Codes: INSUFFICIENT_PERMISSIONS, TEMPORARY_ERROR, SYNC_CURSOR_ERROR, NOT_FOUND, MISCONFIGURED, UNKNOWN\n- Internal retry (3x exponential backoff) on TEMPORARY_ERROR before surfacing\n\nMulti-user:\n- Each user connects their own account\n- Messages deduplicated by header_message_id\n- Participants table links messages to addresses\n- Consumer apps query by participant address to find emails for a contact"
}
